\frac{1}{(k-1)k(k+1)}=\frac{A}{k-1}+\frac{B}{k}+\frac{C}{k+1}
1=Ak(k+1)+B(k-1)(k+1)+Ck(k-1)
\Leftrightarrow 1=Ak^2+Ak+Bk^2-B+Ck^2-Ck
\Leftrightarrow 1=(A+B+C)k^2+(A-C)k-B
A+B+C=0
A-C=0
B=-1
\Rightarrow A=B=1/2
